editorialSummary.text: Stylish, modern restaurant chain serving European & international favourites, plus a kids' menu.

text.text:
People say this pizza restaurant serves delicious Italian food, including pizza, pasta, and seafood dishes, as well as tasty desserts and drinks. They also highlight the good value, friendly and attentive service, and pleasant atmosphere.

Other reviews mention the food can be inconsistent.

originalText.text:
The food in Wildwood restaurant is so delicious. I ate the lasagne, which was recommended by me by our waiter and for desert i had a cookie cheesecake. Both dishes were very tasty.
Adding to that our waiter Faizul was super kind made us feel very welcome.
We will definitely come back soon.

originalText.text: I recently had a superb meal at Wildwood! The British rib-eye steak was absolutely fabulous, definitely a highlight. The service was top-notch—everyone was so warm and friendly, and they really made me feel welcome. It was impressively clean with a lovely atmosphere, and I couldn’t fault the drink selection either. All in all, it was a perfect experience and I’ll definitely be back soon!

originalText.text: When we arrived, it was packed, and we had no reservation. Fortunately, we didn’t wait too long to get a table for two. The waiter who took our orders knew the menu well and made great suggestions. When I ordered my seafood pasta, he recommended less chili, which was perfect. It’s definitely worth a visit if you’re in the area.

originalText.text: I walked past and decided to give this place a go, and I’m so glad I did! The food was lovely, especially the Piccante Carne and Torta della Nonna – both were spot on in taste and presentation. The service was top-notch, with a warm welcome and prompt attentiveness throughout. The atmosphere had a nice vibe, and everything was squeaky clean. I’ll definitely be back for more!

originalText.text:
I liked it that they welcomed us even with walk in on a busy Saturday night and all the more when a neighbourhood restaurant despite booking couldn’t welcome us and was not at all accommodating since we were early there.

Having tried wildwood in chelmsford previously, we preferred to dine here.
We were being served by Samir, he was kind & patient & he remembered not to add mushrooms in repeat order of Grilled courgette pizza even though we missed to mention & despite being so very busy.

In food, we had ordered Grilled courgette & goats cheese pizza ; vegetable primavera; super food salad ; truffle & cheese fries and focaccia.
The food was decent though I would have preferred pizza to be more hot.
Repeat order of goats cheese pizza was served hot & that was delicious.

Good option to dine in when around covent garden
